76561197971254947,Not Recommended,227860,16035682,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,Terrak,"After a year or so of not playing Castle Story, I recently came back to it and soon ran into a new patch whichbroke the gamefor me. I decided to wait a few weeks for them to fix it — the one that froze the game with constant lag after about an hour and a half of playing the same map, and when you reach a certain number of people. Over a month later, there is still no fix.(As of the 26th of June, I have tested the latest patches... it's still going on)When I add that situation to how long this game has taken in the past, until now, to actually have updates implemented, I have to give this one a rather big no for my recommendation. This game has so much potential, and I mean a lot, but there is definitely an issue with the very slow development team, and the lack of progress made when an update is actually released — not much has actually been implemented long term, and important parts of the game are still disabled by the developers because they don't work properly (such as digging).I follow a lot of early access games and this is thepoorest development cycleI am aware of at the moment.Negatives(As of June 2015 with 'bleeding edge' version)-The way the UI is set-up for building, placing items, etc, is atrocious. You have to drill down through so many selections to reach what you want to reach, then you have to get back out if you want to do something else.. it's a bit like torture.  (This is the worst thing about the game for me)-The Save/Load menu is bulky, and slow to use. This needs polishing. (small issue though)-Very slow progression with the development of the game-The radius with cutting down trees. You have to keep adding 'flags' every time you want to cut down a group of trees, and this is rather tedious.-Major performance issues when reaching a certain number of people on screen-The way blue crystal is put into crates by default (again, tedious to manually move it to the actual blue crystal)-The lack of maps on survival. There needs to be a variety here based on peoples play styles, such as a corner start, instead of in the middle. This would greatly improve the game for a lot of people.-The waves(enemies) come too fast. There needs to be an option to manage waves before beginning the game-The fact you have to place a clean up broom radius flag… they should just clean up automatically, or the stuff that needs cleaning up should disappear over time. (tedious to manage, and the little bits littering the ground slow the game down)Positives(As of June 2015 with 'bleeding edge' version)-Friendly fire, but this can get annoying (needs fine tuning)-Variety of enemies (needs fine tuning)-The types of structures you can build using stone or wood. This is rather fun and is really the main point of the game.-The cuteness of the game. The yellow guys and the grey guys are all very cute and make cute noises.-Having your archers take out the enemy is rather enjoyable once you have enough of them, and a system in place where you know exactly where to place them, and how to build your defences.-The quick response of the developers to forum posts is very supportive & commendable-The music is quite good, but there needs to be more variety."
