,Not Recommended,227860,8584141,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,Lonerwurld,"TLDR: Looks can be deceiving.At the time of writing, the game is only early access.  As usual, you shouldn't expect too much - the game will be glitchy and buggy, and my opinion of the game takes that into account.Castle Story is basically another sandbox dwarf-fortress-ish game that appears to take a different approach by using much simpler game mechanics.  You don't have to worry about needs such as food and water, but rather just focus on building a functional castle that can defend against attacks.What I like- It looks cool!  It's got the puffy white clouds, the very simple-looking avatars (bricktrons), the lego-like castle building blocks, etc.,- The gameplay is very simple, it has a refined-looking design, something that appeals to me.What I don't like- Although being early-access, the game is barely playable.  I tried really hard to enjoy the game, but couldn't.  I fully expect to find bugs in a beta, but this title is mostly all looks, the gameplay itself is very bad.- There's not much to do in the game - when I say there's not much to do, I mean what you see in those screens is about it.  You can build some stone and wood blocks, and that's about it.This game shouldn't be early access - it should've stayed out of Steam until it was much more ready than this.  The vibe I got after playing is that the developers - while they might mean well - are an inexperienced group desperately reaching for what funding they can get.Here's a good discussion thread for more info.  I came back to it recently to find it locked - which seemed quite unnecessary.  This is another bad sign imo:http://steamcommunity.com/app/227860/discussions/0/648814844593898025/#p10"
