76561198006545785,Recommended,227860,34605287,Posted: 30 August,all,Rococho Ranger,"Please don't be put off by the ""mixed"" review status.  It is largely because of a lot of the negative reviews when the game was still buggy during Early Access.Regarding the above, this isn't a game I ever thought I would recommend.  I was one of the early backers, and when it was released as a playable beta it was clumsy, buggy as hell and very dissappointing.  I choked it up as wasted money and uninstalled.  When I got the notice that it had hit full release I decided to try it again, and I'm damn glad I did.In the last 2 weeks I have sunk nearly 30 hours into this.  The gameplay is a little tricky to get the hang of, but once you think in the right way it runs very smoothly.  The AI has great pathing, there is great variety in tactics and the three modes allow very different ways to play.there are a couple things I'd like them to introduce, such as a way to copy/store the blueprints of buildings you create and a way to zoom to the unfinished parts of a task.  But over all I am loving the game, and can see myself sinking a hell of a lot more time into it.An early access success if you ask me.  I just hope more people give it a second go and reconsider their first reviews."
76561198000567382,Recommended,227860,28611167,"Posted: 24 December, 2016",all,aduda,"While I get the frustration with waiting eons for a game's completion, there are clear indicators before purchasing that this game is incomplete. The game has bugs, but they're squashed relatively quickly thanks to a responsive and dedicated development team. The game could have more content, but your expectations should have been lowered when you saw this was early access. Plus the mechanics and gameplay are clean and, from watching earlier videos, have clearly been iterated on with care.I don't feel like I've been lied to by the devs about this game's state, and for an early access game I've had a tremendous amount of fun playing it. I look forward to Castle Story's completion whenever it happens, and I hope the devs aren't discouraged by the negative reviews that solely cite the game's slow dev schedule.tl;dr Manage your expectations before buying this or any game. Like a good early access game, mechanics are solid, gameplay is fun if you like RTS-type games that are more in the micro management end of the spectrum, content was lacking but is now solid and constantly improving."
