,Not Recommended,227860,17644726,"Posted: 21 August, 2015",all,shadowbranch,"Two years this has been released on early access and it has yet to actullay get finished, reasonably playable or functional. It's a game with a great idea behind it. I love the thought of building a castle and defending it. The issues I have are how this has been executed and the lack of care by the dev team. I've watched this played and I've played it. It doesn't take more than an hour or two to realize that it has some big flaws that need fixing.Once of the biggest issues I've found is that archers, whom you want on towers to get the best shot angle, will randomly decide to run off your tower, killing themselves instantly. This is very frustrating as even the infrantry units will run up a ram to the top of a wall and dive off to their deaths.There are lots of other issues like the controls menu not being properly completed, it still shows the control defined names in the code. The graphics options are bad, even for a Unity game, there can be so many more choices on how to change the graphics.Ideas on how to do basically anything is non-existant. There is a tutorial yes, extremely basic, but it works. It doesn't tell you how to do other tasks like removing blocks, removing tasks or the like.Overall, this is a great idea, just very very very poorly executed. You might get an hour or two of fun out of it. If you are willing to stick with it, deal with the stupid issues that should be fixed, and make it work, then you can get a few more hours out of it.BTW, Multiplayer is non-existant, so that's a big lie there."
,Recommended,227860,34168398,Posted: 11 August,all,jpotts1515gaming,"First off ignore the hate for the game. Most of the early reviews where because this game was put on ea way before it was ready back in 13'. Now that the game has had 4 years to get its self together it is one of the best games. Think RTS meets minecraft. The way it handles ai is great. Workers use their ""brains"" way better than most games. For example if  you tell them to do something they will do that and any other tasks associated with order unless u tell them not to. So if u chop trees down they will auto pick them up and store them unless u say no. This makes it way easier to play but still gives u tons of options. Overall a great game that has huge potential. Check the new reviews because the overall is no longer accurate. NOTE i purchased this yesterday so this is my first impressions and i will update review after more time. Thanks for reading my review"
