76561197961414846,Recommended,227860,22833359,"Posted: 6 May, 2016",all,Onliuge,"Even though I recommend this game, it's really recommended to a more specific group than just to everyone.Pros:- Developers are quite interactive with the community on their youtube page ""sauropodstudio"" where you can ask questions as they stream the game every Friday at 3pm US Central time.- Bugs are few in number and if reported correctly are taken care of quickly.- Controls are easy to use for RTS veterans and easy to learn for everyone else.- Pathfinding, for your troops, is well developed for a building RTS.- *Personal Taste* The graphical fedelity is pleasing to the eye.- *Personal Taste* The gameplay is simple so not to have unneeded extras.Cons:- The game requires a reasonably powerful computer setup to play on anything but simple graphics.- The game is run on Unity engine which makes the game choppy when you get into later levels with larger waves of enemies.- *Personal Taste* Some of the more interesting additions have yet to be added to the game.- The AI pathing for the enemies can be exploited to make the game trivial.- *Personal Taste* For the current amount of content, the price is a little too high.- It has no real tutorial so you'll have to watch videos, or look at the wiki for help.- Development is slow due to their small team.Recommendation is to RTS fans, who cross over with Building fans, such as minecraft, with those who enjoy an easier simpler form of Dwarf Fortress. Buy only if you really believe that the developers vision of the outcome of the game matches your own and you you don't mind waiting for it to be worked out by there relatively small team."
