76561197970782320,Not Recommended,227860,9556416,"Posted: 18 March, 2014",all,elandryl,"***EDIT 03-15-2016***""Just forget about this game for the next two or three years"", I said... two years ago.Castle Story is now far more functionnal. Your bricktrons have made tremendous progress in their pathfinding - they now DO manage to go where you ask them. They might still be a bit... slow to accomplish what you order them to do, but eventually, they will succeed - if what you asked them is possible, of course, and you might need a few try & retry to understand their particular logic. But still, as a sandbox game, it manages to realize a good part of what it was supposed to realize - wich is good.""So why is your review still negative?"", might you ask. Well, the answer is quite simple: right now, the game still isn't fun.First of all, the bricktrons are slow, and building anything takes a HUGE amount of time. The IA isn't exactly helping about that, and it is a shame that the devs still haven't thought about the first button you would think of in this game - a button to fast forward, that is.Second, there are little options in the matter of building. A few stone bricks, a few woodlogs (very complicated to use, by the way), you should be building very little variations of the same model of towers and walls pretty quickly. After two or three hours, the game is already awfully repetitive.That's were the ""invasion"" mode might get fun: testing the resistance of your citadel by repelling infinite waves of ennemies. Well, problem is: too few ennemies variations, too few units, and most of all, the IA is a mess and cannot hope to compete with any RTS' AI. Your archers might actually be more dangerous for you own troops, and the knights never do anything right; and of course, you have no real control about the attitude they should use. So, for now, the strategy is rather plain: build a tall tower, put all your achers on top of it, rince, repeat. And pray that the ennemies don't get at the base of the tower, for your bricktrons are too dumb to lean and shoot downward. And, to make matter worse, repairing any damaged structure is a real pain in the back, as your bricktron can't seem to fix anything beyond their reach, their reach being something around two yards high. Of course, that's precisely the height where the ennemies like to dig (sigh).So it appears that I still was awfully optimistic when I told people to wait for two or three years: right now, I do believe that Castle Story will finally be a fun and fully working game around the year 2020.*** *** *** ***ORIGINAL REVIEW:This looks like a hit. This smells like a hit. Too bad, for months now it's been nothing but a buggy, twice-in-a-year-updated wreck of a game. Your builders are stupid, they can't do anything right. Nothing of what you see in the trailers is actually doable right now. So, my two cents: just forget about this game for the next two or three years, maybe it' ll become something that you might actually call ""a game"". Right now it's an expensive prank."
