,Recommended,227860,28694912,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,Sir Dinga,"Having sunk hours upon hours into this game I can safely say, this is an incredible game in its own right.Whilst updates are rather infrequent with new content being added every 2 months or so, the game itself is endless fun. It does take a while to wrap your head around a few of the building mechanics but after doing so it is ridiculously satisfying, allowing you to build gigantic castles and towers from which your units can attack.The multiplayer is also a lot of fun with a rather bizarre take on a strategy game, rather than building a town to support your units development, you are literally building a castle and a few small outposts to defend shards that you must capture to give yourself an edge in PvP.The one downside I would say this game has is that it is a bit slow to start, however this is remedied by the fact you can summon waves when you are ready for them, meaning you can summon the first 20 or so waves within 20 clicks. This is virtually suicide but if you feel like doing this, go for it.I would highly recommend this game."
