,Recommended,227860,34547832,Posted: 28 August,all,Space Walrus,"Castle Story is a fun, challenging RTS Builder. While the game can be a breeze, it can also kick your butt. Even on Easy mode the AI can rush you down quite quickly if you're not fast enough at mustering a formidable force. The UI is easy to understand for the most part, with the radial menu being nice and smooth to interact with. While not the fastest UI, it's not an RTS about keeping your APM high. Sometimes you'll be able to sit back and watch your Bricktrons do their work. The maps are all unique and offer their own challenge. The game even ships with a built in map-editor and Workshop support.Overall the game is fun and great to sit down with for an hour or two at a time.Since the game was first placed into EA on Steam, I have had this product. I'll admit there was a time when I was doubtful of it's release. But the developers kept with the project and turned it into a fine, fun game. Castle Story has changed dramatically since it's first iterations and all for the better. The UI improved, new classes for Bricktrons, new stations for crafting, new materials to craft. However, even with new additions the game never got too complicated. New materials were easy to craft, and weren't overwhelming. New systems are easy to understand and get a hang of. Perhaps the best addition is working multiplayer. You can create maps for your friends and you to play on, either in a 2vCorrupton match, or 1v1s, or if you so desire a larger free for all scenario.A lot of the reviews on Steam are woes about the Early Access, or about how long it took, or how the game didn't live up to their expectation because it should be amazing after being a five year project.The game isn't a masterpiece, no. But it's fun, cute, and a great way to spend your time when you're looking for more casual RTS building experience. I don't feel entitled to some masterpiece just because it's been in development for a while. I never expected that. I expected what was delivered. And I enjoy this game very much.I'd rate this game about a 7 out of 10. It's no masterpiece, but it certainly hits the spot when you're in the mood for it."
