,Recommended,227860,22897688,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,Tamaster,"VERSION 0.6.4 REVIEW===Pros & Cons+ Pros ++ Very good mix of Sandbox, Tower Defence and Strategy that actually works+ You can build your very own fortress and defend it with an army+ Totally destructible / modifiable environment+ Added sandbox mode to build without worry of attacks+ Simple enough control system allows you to do what you need quickly+ AI has improved much since past versions and now can do complex tasks without errors+ Good building system / task system that doesn't make a mess of what is going on and keeps it clean+ Multiplayer has been improved and now works properly+ Good variety, for an Early Access, of parts and structures to build- Cons -- Camera system could be better- You still have to dig resources in sandbox mode, instead of having everything unlimited like a proper ""creative"" mode- Kinda poor variety of units to either build or to face in battle as enemies===Personal opinionCastle Story is surely a game with lots of potential, and still has time and quite a long way to be able to fully express the possibilities available to its gameplay. Still, it has improved a lot since the past versions, devs actually listened to the community on what should be done to improve the game, and did it.This mix of Defense, RTS and Sandbox can be found in very few other games i know of, and it's worth to give a try to anyone who likes building his own stuff and/or RTS in general.It can really be fun to defend your own castle, underground fortress or whatever you want to build against increasingly difficult enemies, think of it as a Stronghold mixed with Minecraft, pretty epic isn't it?I will update this review when updates come out, stay tuned.===ACTUAL RATING: 8/10"
