,Not Recommended,227860,10038956,"Posted: 6 May, 2014",all,Yanni Depper,"What a rocky road this has been - After years in development limbo, moderator banhammer scandals, ""re-factoring"" periods of development with limited communication and a metric♥♥♥♥♥♥ton of feedback from the community, Castle Story is now finally in it's so called ""full release version"".The game presents itself as a light-hearted castle defence sim, and offers one of the most frustrating gameplay experiences I've ever had the misfortune of coming across in this particular genre. The UI is clunk and overly complicated, with many functions being accessed through a poorly designed radial wheel, which is as easy to navigate as the M25 circular on a Friday evening.Despite numerous overalls and fixes, the pathfinding still appears to be one of the biggest issues with the game, with Bricktons standing around like abandonded husbands outside the changing rooms of a clothes store. After being assinged a task, your Briktons will sometimes hopelessly circle around each other, like pensioners in a mosh pit, forcing you to cancel the task that was assigned (after navigating the god-awful radial wheel in order to do so), before recreating it and hoping to whichever deity that you follow that they'll actually follow through this time.The community has also come out with some fantastic builds since the game was launched, but don't kid yourself into thinking that you'll be pulling off the same levels of architectural wonder; building is still a very frustrating task, which requires you to build structures to access upper-level structures and so on. While the idea sounds nice and somewhat immersive in principle, it is executed awfully in this game, and coupled with the already borked path-finding system, leaves you with a sour taste in your mouth, and can put you off the game altogether.Simply put, the developers have farted out 1.0 in order to say that it was finished, and I wouldn't be shocked if continued support for the game died before the start of 2018. I hated the way their moderation team talked to the community, and their apparent disregard for the voices that were offering help have completely being ignored.This game could have been fun a few years ago, but it's nothing short of a pain in the♥♥♥♥♥♥now."
