76561198011819443,Not Recommended,227860,11349212,"Posted: 21 July, 2014",all,Eustace the Monk,"12/10/14 UPDATE: There's a new patch! Nope, nothing in the way of actual content...they've rewritten three major aspects of the game (graphics, AI and new voxel engine). REALLY?! After over two years of development, they're still rewriting the basics. If this doesn't say ""STAY AWAY"" to you, then nothing will.ORIGINAL REVIEW: This might be an awesome building/fight game in about eighteen years or so. I love building games, and as a result I get easily bamboozled by the promise of games like Castle Story -- take charge over a group of vaguely humanoid bipedal lumps named 'bricktons' and have them build castles and buildings and such, make weapons for them so that they can defend themselves against all manner of goblinry. There's gonna be mayhem and fighting and explosions with arrows and stuff flying everywhere. With catapults and everything.Unfortunately, as it stands right now, it's little more than a tech demo -- the UI is flaky, making it difficult to mine and build anything. The Bricktons tend to stand around more often than actually do work due to incomplete AI. Despite excellent graphics and animation, the game itself has a unique lack of polish to it -- it's tough to even know what to do in a logistics sense, and the UI makes doing it a struggle even when you've figured it out.What's worse is that Castle Story has been in development for an amazing length of time for it to be in such a state (just over two years at this point, and their kickstarter has been funded to the tune of $702k when they asked for just under $30k). As best as I can figure out, the development team had to rewrite vast sections of their game for some reason or another at some point last year (rumor has it to accommodate a Linux version, which is preposterous if it's true).However, their development blog of late has been more concerned about their going to PAX East and moving to a new office than trivialities such as the state of their game (and reading between the lines, it would seem as though their time at PAX didn't go so well...which is hardly a surprise given the state of the game currently).All-in-all, avoid Castle Story for now. Hopefully it's coming out in the next two years or so and I can change my recommendation. I play a LOT of early access games, and this one is frankly the second worst when it comes to time in development."
