,Not Recommended,227860,10931888,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,FacePalm.exe,"Rather cute game, which I wasted a few hours on.Now as a disclamer, I do realise that this is an early access game, but as it stands, it is barely playable. At this point the core game should be up and working, with a few minor bugs here and there. (i.e. No major game breaking bugs.)Firstly, I was constantly fighting with the pathfinding/AI of the bricktons (Workers).Half the time they would either get clogged, run on the spot, refuse to be assigned to an objective, become unselectable, sometimes wait 5-10+ secconds to figure out a simple path from A to B, take the longest and most inefficient route and in general; they do not do what I want when I want it. Almost NEVER.You have the choice between two combat units: Archer (Ranged) and Soldier (Melee)The Soldier being useless, as 99% of the time will run past the enemy he's chasing.So you have to basically rely on archers. Except they're prone to shooting each other in the back, and trying to shoot through your resource stashes, destroying them with a single arrow.There are also catapaults, Which i couldn't figure out how to work (Couldn't seem to assign any tasks to them or drop stuff on them)The level design looks cool, but functionally is an absolute pain to deal with.I lost countless resources (Trees and stone) into the abyss thanks to them (especially the trees) being next to the edge and 95% of the time, the physics would tip towards the edge instead of inwards. (And you have no control over how they fall.)There is also no variety in the enemy's you face. Only the one zerg rush type.The save system is also buggy, I saved my first game (After about 1-2 hours of play) and then immedietly reloaded it. (There was a builder looping a falling sound, who was stuck in a mine.) It wouldn't load, so I lost that save.If the other reviews are anything to go by (And the release date of Sept 2013) It doesn't seem like any of these problems will be fixed anytime soon. There have been patches recently, but there are still an absolutly massive number of issues.This is interesting concept, one that I liked the look of, but has been very poorly executed. A majority of it seems to be implemented with Unity's stock-standard features, And it suffers for it.I wouldn't buy it again.TL;DR: Cute but terribly broken game with the outlook of few to no useful updates in the future. Go elsewhere."
