aint on a canvas from before. Annoyed with crate and the french guy I walk away. A couple hours later I decide to check to see if my painting might have done anything. Holy hell, The painting still hasn't changed, I inquire to crate about WTF is going on. He tells me that the painting has changed and shows me a list of things he says has changed but it is still the same damn splash of paint and NOTHING has changed. The french guy is absent, Crate informs me that he went on a buisness trip down the block to promote his painting. Hmmm, should he have something to sell before advertising farther? The french guy comes back shortly after with another guy. They talk and the other guy leaves. I ask crate whats going on and he informs me that the splash of paint on the canvas is all wrong and needs to be corrected. The french guy throws a white sheet over it and says it'll be fixed shortly. An hour later I come back and the two guys are talking about their unveiling of a new improved ""refactored"" version of the painting. The white sheet gets pulled and....ITS THE SAME ♥♥♥♥ING SPLASH OF PAINT from before. I voice my opinion and low and behold, hundreds of people like me are now standing with me wanting answers. Crate answers some, but most are silenced with a quick hammer to their heads. An hour later, I decide to check on it, I'm not sure why at this point, perhaps it's the mentality to watch a train wreck occur, you know it's going to sad but also like, HOLY ♥♥♥♥, did you see that guys brains go flying all over. Anyways, you'll never guess whats happened, that's right, NOTHING....that splash of paint is still there, but now theres another painting right next to it with marks pointing to the other painting saying that this white part of the canvas is almost done while this smear hasn't even been started. I'm not even sure where to begin here, I still have yet to be told what this painting will be in the end, I was told I would enjoy it, but so far 93% of the people that bought this painting, HATE IT....."
