76561198204066583,Not Recommended,227860,34896136,Posted: 11 September,all,LadyLassy,"I really wanted to like this game, but it's just too flawed. Both the single player and multiplayer modes left me frustrated. The AI that manages your workers has a lot of problems. The pacing is REALLY SLOW. The combat, tunneling, and crafting mechanics are difficult to manage and the AI tends to trip over itself, forcing you to go in and micro your units for basic tasks. Honestly, this game should be in Beta so that the developers can get the feedback that they clearly need.A few examples of things that really annoyed me:1. I had plenty of planks, rope, and fabric stockpiled next to a workbench. I tried multiple times to make archer kits. Nothing happened. Then, I tried directly assigning a Bricktron to the task. The worker wandered around aimlessly for several seconds before giving up and moving to another task. Mind you, I was desperately trying to fend off an attack while this was happening.2. Many times, you go to build a wall, and the AI isn't smart enough to build it in the right order to avoid creating impassable obstructions or walling out your workers.3. You just don't have very many workers, and they tend to do stupid things, making their tasks go slow. Supposedly, you are supposed to expand your base and get more workers using capture wards. I never got that far, since it takes a while to make wards, they are very vulnerable to attacks, and you constantly have to babysit the AI. Don't forget, you can't just tell them to build a ward (even though it's a ""structure""), you have to ""craft"" it, THEN have a worker place it as part of a ""construction task.""4. Iron is challenging to obtain, especially since you have no idea if a particular tunnel or quarry might produce some. This is a problem given how important the resource is to crafting.This game can't decide if it's a castle building simulator, a tower/castle defense game, a crafting game, an RTS game, etc. It tries to do too much and ends up doing it poorly. If a ""version 2"" of this game comes out, I might be interested in taking another look, but not until then."
