76561198001536271,Not Recommended,227860,21210581,"Posted: 14 February, 2016",all,odhan,"Around 18 months ago I reviewed this game and gave it a thumbs down. I saw a video of someone playing it on YouTube and decided it had been long enough to see if the game had improved. I can see there's been a lot of development, new features and a general improvement in the completeness of the game. However, there are many frustrating aspects that prevent me from giving this a thumbs up.Possibly the most important part of this game, the AI of the Bricktrons, is also the most unsatisfying. Your workers will rarely do what you expect them to do, they drop resources instead of storing them, they don't start jobs when there are jobs available and they store resources in the wrong place. Those 3 aspects form what I would consider the core of the game and they do not work. It should be effortless to direct your workers to store materials in a designated stockpile, but it is not. If you have a stockpile full of wood and you set it to store only stone, you would expect your workers to move the wood, but of course they don't.Then there's the UI, this is a stong example of different not always being good. I am left with a feeling of tedium and frustration from the entire experience.This game has been in development for too long to have these flaws. Who knows when this game will be good or finished, if ever. I highly doubt I'll be back in another year to see if it's any different, but maybe I will, I do normally really enjoy these types of games.My original review from Feb 2016:This game is pants. Such unintuitive controls, pointless gameplay that leaves you frustrated. I bought it ages ago and have tried to revive it in my library a few times, to no avail. Maybe I'll come back to it in another year, but I imagine it'll still be in alpha and will still be unsatisfying."
