76561198012102532,Not Recommended,227860,15127619,"Posted: 30 March, 2015",all,dblclkmatt,"Imagine a castle building game where you build dense walls to survive hordes of enemies, and use soldiers and catapults to repel their swelling mass at your doorstep. That is not this game. At least not the way that you might imagine it.I am aware that the game is still in beta when making this review and I can forgive things like work queue locking up, or the path finding of the workers taking them around the map instead of through the door I built for them. However, that does not excuse the terrible selection process, which is pivotal and my primary gripe.I purchase the game over 6 months ago, played it, got frustrated with it, but I did not condemn it. I reserved my opinion with the it's beta status in mind. So I came back recently, hoping that game had advanced and ironed out the problems. They did advance it and supply two game modes instead of one, and some prefabbed worlds, however my biggest issue still remained.Selecting your units is hit or miss, at best. Don't trust the drag select box. and don't trust shift/ctrl selecting either. You have select individuals and give them commands as individuals... assuming you can select them. The cursor will hover right above the intended target and somehow the hit box is not responding. So if you're ever in a pinch and you need to move your workers, might as well kiss them goodbye. You click frantically to simply select them and they die in the process after one hit.It was very frustrating seeing how my next issue is with the recruiting of new units. Maybe I'm missing something, but I've two dozen little stars floating around my crystal... why are they ALL used to make ONE unit? When later on there are only a few stars and it seems to be enough for that one unit. Hell, sometimes I've got plenty of stars and I can't make a unit. It was inconsistent and made no sense.The game otherwise is fine. Not really edge of you seat type stuff, but it fills whatever child-hood need there is to build massive structures with nothing but blocks, and then see it crash down when you knock it down. Not much in the sound department, and the graphics are very bright and friendly. I wish the enemies had more to offer, however since it's really easy to bottle neck them and shower them with arrows.With the problems, and low replay value, I can't recommend this game."
